==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek [[διαλογικός]] (''dialogikos'') "related to a [[dialogue]]", from ancient Greek [[διάλογος]] (''dialogos'') "conversation, discourse, [[dialogue]]".

===Adjective===
'''dialogic'''
# of, or related to [[dialogue]]
#(''of a literary work'') written in dialogue

